President Mnangagwa is welcomed by his Democratic Republic of Congo counterpart President Joseph Kabila in Kinshasa yesterday. — (Picture by Presidential Photographer Joseph Nyadzayo) Nduduzo Tshuma in Kinshasa, DRC PRESIDENT Emmerson Mnangagwa just toured the College of High Studies for Strategy and Defense here. The college, a brain child of President Joseph Kabila, is a specialised military institution established in 2016. President Mnangagwa was received at the institution by the Country’s Defense Minister Chrispin Atamatabe. Minister Atamatabe gave a brief history of the institution which is a brain child of DRC President Joseph Kabila. President Mnangagwa said he was impressed by the facility as it goes a long way in creating African based solutions on defense and security. He said he was also fascinated by the fact that the institution accepts foreign military students.